===Etymology===
A learned borrowing from {{learned borrowing|en|la|aberrātiō|gloss=relief, diversion|notext=1}}, first attested in 1594 <ref>[http://dictionary.reference.com/browse/aberration Aberration at Dictionary.com]</ref>, from {{m|la|aberrō||wander away, go astray}}, from {{m|la|ab||away}} + {{m|la|errō||wander}}<ref>{{R:CDOE|page=2}}</ref>. Compare French {{m|fr|aberration}}. See also {{m|en|aberrate}}.

===Pronunciation===
